 for bestpractices and # Host Listing Create / Edit

## Overview
Build a premium Host Listing Create / Edit page for Roam Resort that enables hosts to create, edit, and manage destination listings and editorial content. This page combines a multi-tab form, media management (image gallery with drag-and-drop, crop, reorder, captions), SEO metadata, publish controls, and validation. It must be robust, accessible, and runtime-safe, guarding against null/undefined values for all array operations and API responses as per project-wide coding standards.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
This page is the primary content creation surface for hosts to publish and refine Roam Resort listings. Goals:
- Provide a guided, multi-tab form to capture all facets of a destination: Basic Info, Editorial Content, Gallery, Experience Details, and SEO Metadata.
- Offer an integrated media manager for uploading, rearranging, cropping, and captioning images (Cloudinary direct uploads recommended).
- Support lifecycle controls: Save Draft, Preview, Publish/Unpublish, and Clear/Reset.
- Validate inputs with helpful guidance texts and enforce content guidelines (title length, image specs, word counts, required fields).
- Integrate with existing host authentication and authorization flows; show read-only views of related inquiries (as applicable to hosts).
- Ensure accessibility (aria-labels, keyboard navigation, proper focus management).
- Ensure data safety and consistency with the API layer: correct data shapes, defaults, and type-safe operations.
- Provide responsive, editorial UI aligned with Roam Resort’s luxury aesthetic: large imagery, restrained typography, and a calm color system.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Multi-tab layout:
  - Basic Info: title, tagline, destination category, location (city/country), map embed or coordinates (optional).
  - Editorial Content: rich text editor for overview, narrative, and highlights.
  - Gallery Upload: drag-and-drop area with cropping, reordering, and per-image captions; Cloudinary direct upload flow; per-image metadata (alt text, caption, order).
  - Experience Details: amenities, capacity, sleeping arrangements, accessibility, activities, and check-in/check-out details.
  - SEO Metadata: slug, meta title, meta description, open graph tags, canonical URL, robots.
- Publish Controls:
  - Save Draft, Preview (open a live preview or modal), Publish/Unpublish toggle with confirmation.
  - Validation indicators and inline help text near fields.
- Validation & Help Text:
  - Image specs (min/max size, aspect ratios, formats), word counts for editorial content, required fields, and recommended lengths.
- Visual guidance:
  - Cards with large hero imagery at top of sections, soft shadows, and subtle borders.
  - Buttons: bronze-gold (#A97C50) with white or navy text; secondary actions in warm beige (#ECE1D4) with bronze outlines.
  - Editable sections use generous spacing (40–80px). Internal card padding 24–32px.

Connected API integrations (where applicable):
- Submit listing data to backend via REST/GraphQL endpoints for create and update.
- Image upload process via Cloudinary (direct upload) with returned URLs stored in listing data.
- SEO metadata saved alongside listing data.
- No external UI data dependencies beyond host-provided content.

## Components to Build
- HostListingCreateEditPage
  - State management for active tab, form data, and loading states.
  - Data schema normalization with safety checks (nullish coalescing and Array checks).
- MultiTabNavigator
  - Tab headers with active state, keyboard navigation, and responsive behavior.
- TextField, TextArea, and Select components
  - Reusable, accessible, with error messaging and inline help.
- RichTextEditor
  - Lightweight WYSIWYG or Markdown editor with clean integration and sanitization.
- GalleryUploader
  - Drag-and-drop zone, image cropping, per-image metadata, reorderable grid, and direct Cloudinary upload flow.
  - Ensure image specs are surfaced in UI and validated before submission.
- MediaCard
  - Card for each image with thumbnail, caption input, order handle, alt text, and delete action.
- ExperienceDetailsForm
  - Amenities (checkbox/select), capacity (number), sleeping arrangements, accessibility, activities.
- SEOEditor
  - Slug creator, meta title, meta description, Open Graph fields, canonical URL, robots meta.
- PublishControls
  - Save Draft, Preview, Publish/Unpublish toggle with state-dependent labels and confirmations.
- Preview Pane / Modal
  - Live rendering of listing as host would see it; separate modal or route-based preview.
- ValidationSummary
  - Aggregates and displays validation errors with field-level guidance.
- APIService
  - Centralized API calls for create/update, fetch existing listing (for edit), and image/upload responses.
- Utils
  - Safe array handling, null guards, and type guards for API responses.

Technical specifics:
- All array-like data should be guarded: use (data ?? []) and Array.isArray checks where applicable.
- Initialize state with correct types: useState<YourType[]>([]) and appropriate defaults.
- Validate API responses: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Optional chaining for nested API results: obj?.field?.nested.
- Data models should reflect null-safety: default to empty strings or empty objects as needed.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework: React + TypeScript (prefer React 18 with hooks).
- State management: Local component state with useState and useReducer for complex sections; optionally context for sharing across tabs.
- Accessibility: ARIA roles, aria-live regions for validation messages, keyboard navigable tabs, and proper focus management after tab switches or modals.
- Styling: Consume design system tokens; implement with CSS-in-JS (Emotion/styled-components) or CSS modules consistent with project.
- Media manager specifics:
  - Drag-and-drop area supports reordering via drag handles.
  - Crop tool integration or light-weight cropping before upload.
  - Cloudinary direct upload integration: unsigned/presigned uploads; handle upload progress and error states.
  - Per-image fields: caption, alt text, order index.
- Form validation:
  - Real-time validation for required fields, image limits, and content guidelines.
  - Image specs warnings (e.g., "minimum 3 images", "JPEG/PNG only", "min 1200x800").
  - Word count limits for editorial content.
- Data submission:
  - On Save Draft: persist only draft fields.
  - On Publish: require all required fields, run full validation, and then call API.
  - Optimistic UI updates with rollback on failure.
- Data normalization:
  - Always ensure arrays are defined: const gallery = list?.gallery ?? [].
  - Normalize strings to trimmed values, handle undefined gracefully.

### Backend
- API Endpoints (examples; adjust to project conventions):
  - POST /api/hosts/listings -> create listing
  - PUT /api/hosts/listings/{id} -> update listing
  - GET /api/hosts/listings/{id} -> fetch listing for edit
  - POST /api/upload/image -> handle Cloudinary signature or upload (if centralized)
  - GET /api/hosts/listings/{id}/inquiries -> read-only related inquiries (for hosts, optional)
- Database Tables (conceptual):
  - listings: id, host_id, title, tagline, category, location_city, location_country, slug, editorial_content, seo_title, seo_description, og_image, is_published, created_at, updated_at, etc.
  - listing_gallery: id, listing_id, image_url, caption, alt_text, sort_order
  - listing_amenities: listing_id, amenity_id (or denormalized list)
  - listing_experience: listing_id, capacity, bedrooms, beds, bathrooms, accessibility, activities_json
  - listing_metadata: listing_id, meta_title, meta_description, canonical_url, robots
- Validation & business rules:
  - Ensure required fields exist before publish (title, editorial content length, at least 3 images, etc.).
  - Transaction-like operations to save listing and related media atomically when possible.

### Integration
- Data flows:
  - Host creates/edits listing data; media manager uploads images; image URLs stored in listing_gallery.
  - Editorial content stored in listing fields; SEO metadata stored in listing_metadata.
  - Publish toggle updates is_published flag and triggers visibility rules.
  - Preview uses a sanitized, read-only rendering of listing data.
- State synchronization:
  - On loading edit page, fetch listing data safely (null checks); initialize UI with defaults if data missing.
  - After save/publish, refresh listing state and show success toast with actions (View listing, Continue editing).

## User Experience Flow
1. Host logs in and navigates to Host Dashboard > Listings > Create/Edit.
2. On Create, multi-tab form loads with Basic Info tab active.
3. Host fills required basic fields; receives inline validation prompts as needed.
4. Host uses Editorial Content tab to add rich narrative; word count/format hints appear.
5. Host uploads and manages Gallery:
   - Drag-and-drop to reorder; crop and adjust each image; add captions and alt text.
   - Cloudinary direct upload validates file types and size; show progress and errors.
6. Host completes Experience Details with amenities and capacity; ensures required info present.
7. Host sets SEO Metadata in SEO tab; composes meta title/description; sets slug.
8. Host uses Publish Controls:
   - Save Draft to store progress.
   - Preview to view editorial layout and public-facing appearance.
   - Publish to make listing live or Unpublish to hide.
9. If validation errors exist, helper text highlights issues; host corrects and saves again.
10. On successful publish, listing appears in public destination pages and host can monitor inquiries (read-only) and manage interactions.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:
  - Listing
    - id: string
    - hostId: string
    - title: string
    - tagline: string
    - category: string
    - locationCity: string
    - locationCountry: string
    - slug: string
    - editorialContent: string
    - seoTitle: string
    - seoDescription: string
    - ogImage: string
    - isPublished: boolean
    - createdAt: string
    - updatedAt: string
  - ListingGallery
    - id: string
    - listingId: string
    - imageUrl: string
    - caption: string
    - altText: string
    - sortOrder: number
  - ListingAmenities (or amenities array on Listing)
  - ListingExperience
    - listingId: string
    - capacity: number
    - bedrooms: number
    - beds: number
    - bathrooms: number
    - amenities: string[]
    - accessibility: string
  - ListingMetadata
    - listingId: string
    - metaTitle: string
    - metaDescription: string
    - canonicalUrl: string
    - robots: string

- API Endpoints:
  - POST /api/hosts/listings
  - PUT /api/hosts/listings/{id}
  - GET /api/hosts/listings/{id}
  - POST /api/upload/image (Cloudinary integration)
  - GET /api/hosts/listings/{id}/inquiries (optional in host view)
  - Additional endpoints for validation or search as needed

- Security:
  - Ensure host authentication (JWT/session) and authorization to create/edit listings.
  - Validate ownership on fetch/update to prevent cross-user edits.
  - CSRF protection for forms; secure image upload endpoints.

- Validation:
  - Title: required, length 5–100.
  - Editorial Content: required, minimum word count (e.g., 150 words).
  - Gallery: at least 3 images, up to 20; each image size constraints; altText required.
  - Location: city and country required.
  - SEO: meta title/description required with reasonable lengths.
  - Slug: URL-safe, unique per host (server-side check).

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Host Listing Create page loads with all tabs and components present and accessible.
- [ ] All fields have proper validation; invalid inputs show inline help and prevent publish.
- [ ] Gallery uploader supports drag-and-drop, cropping, caption/alt text per image, and Cloudinary upload flow.
- [ ] Data submission uses null-safe accessors; API responses are validated (response?.data guardrails).
- [ ] Saving as Draft persists data; Publish toggles update is_published and makes listing visible to guests after validation.
